  "original_title": "No action against arrested undergrads under PTA: Govt. assures",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "No action against arrested undergrads under PTA: Govt. assures",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The government today assured that the group of university students who were arrested yesterday during a protest would not be dealt with Prevention of Terrorism Act (PTA).",
        "Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena gave this assurance in response to a question raised by Opposition Leader Sajith Premadasa.",
        "The Opposition Leader said a group of 25 university students of the Inter University Student Federation (IUSF) have been arrested during a protest and questioned as to whether they would be detained under PTA.",
        "He said university students had not caused any damages to state or private property and that they had only exercised their right to protest.",
        "\"The government has unleashed state terrorism against the protesters. Have people been scrapped of their political rights, right to dissent? he questioned. The Prime Minister said the government was not hoping to take action against the arrested students inder PTA and that action would be taken against them under the general laws. (Ajith Siriwardana and Yohan Perera)"
      ],
